Implementation in Verilog of the well-known game Tetris. The program is intended for synthesis on an FPGA and supports the VGA standard. The repository also contains a simulation allowing the game to be run in a local environment.

Main components:

 ðŸ”¸  Tetris: Top-level module containing the game logic and instantiating the remaining modules.
 ðŸ”¸  VGA_sync: Circuit controlling the control signals for the VGA output.
 ðŸ”¸  color_generator: Determines the displayed color in a combinational manner.
 ðŸ”¸  pseudo_random_number_generator: Relies on a 9-bit shift register with linear feedback (feedback polynomial: x^9 + x^4 + 1).

Prerequisites for running the simulation:

 ðŸ”¸  Verilator
 ðŸ”¸  g++
 ðŸ”¸  CImg

To run the simulation:

verilator -cc --trace Tetris.v --exe tb_tetris.cpp

Replace the generated VTetris.mk file with the one from the repository.

make -C obj_dir -f VTetris.mk VTetris
